categoryData.promoMessage:
Most professional environments rely heavily on paper for their printing needs. Whether it's a corporation that goes through reams a day on sales collateral or a family restaurant printing extra menus, businesses of all sizes can benefit from copy paper sold at Staples.

How Is Paper Packaged?

Paper packaging depends on the type of paper being purchased from Staples. For example, most copy paper typically comes packaged in reams, which is a standard unit containing 500 sheets. If you need many reams, consider buying cartons of copy paper in bulk. Each carton contains a set number of reams.

Other types of paper like color paper are sold by the number of sheets per pack. Colored paper sold at Staples typically ranges in size from 250 sheets to 5,000 sheets. Index cards are also available in bulk, but more commonly range from 50 to 100 cards per pack.

What Sizes of Paper Are Available?

In general, standard paper sizes will vary depending on the type of paper. Thats why the standard sizes for index cards will not be the same as the standard sizes for colored paper or notepads.

However, there are four common printer paper sizes throughout North America: junior legal, legal, letter and tabloid.

  • Junior legal size: 8 x 5 inches
  • Legal size: 8.5 x 14 inches
  • Letter size: 8.5 x 11 inches
  • Tabloid size: 11 x 17 inches

While letter size is great for both academic and business purposes as well as general use, the legal and junior sizes of paper proliferate the law industry in the form of legal pads. The tabloid size, also known as the ledger size, is used to make small newspapers or tabloids.

What Are Common Types of Paper?

While copy or printer paper may be what is traditionally thought of when referring to paper, there are a multitude of types of paper and paper-based items available at Staples.

In addition to copy or printer paper, there is also colored paper, cardstock paper, stationery paper, index cards and more. Pair your chosen style of paper with our selection of office supplies to come up with creative projects.

Are All Types of Paper Recyclable?

Yes and no. Most kinds of paper are recyclable, but there are some exceptions. Fresh paper and paper with ink or pencil markings are safe to recycle, however once papers come into contact with paint, they are no longer recyclable.

Most colored paper is recyclable, but some isnt. A quick way to be sure is to tear off a corner and see if it is white in the middle. If so, recycle it! If not, toss it in the garbage to be safe or contact your local recycling center to learn more.

Which paper is not recyclable no matter its condition? Do not recycle:

  • Paper with any sticky adhesive
  • Paper that has been shredded, as the fibers are too short for the recycling process
  • Any type of wax paper

As always, be sure to check with your local waste management authorities prior to recycling items you are unsure of.

text.value:
Paper and stationery products come in many shapes and sizes. Choose copy and multipurpose paper to print important business documents or memos for your company. Pre-printed awards and certificates make it easy to recognize excellent service or sales.

Business Cards
Design business cards that will reflect your business and make a lasting impression. Create custom business cards online using the easy design tool on Staples Copy & Print. Choose from a variety of finishes and card stock to make your business cards really stand out!

Versatile Office Supplies
Paper and stationery give you control over how your office communications look. Print marketing messages for distribution to customers and vendors, or craft professional memos for peers and coworkers. The exceptional versatility of paper supplies makes it easy to tailor the look of your message to the audience.

Marketing Support
Loyalty cards and blank card stock can both help your marketing team distribute your message to customers and clients. Loyalty cards make it easy to track customer transactions and reward loyal patrons for their continued business, and blank card stock allows you to print punch cards for returning customers or create business cards for your employees. To ensure a clean and professional look when working with card stock and loyalty cards, try high-quality paper trimmers.

Specialized Paper
Paper and stationery products include specialized options that assist with everyday business operations. These include thermal paper for point-of-sale transaction tracking and receipts as well as preprinted forms for tracking accounts payable and receivable. Specialized paper products can dramatically increase efficiency.

Heavy-Duty Options
Thick sheets of acid-free paper are excellent tools for saving information that needs to last for years. Use this archival paper to store printed copies of important business documents, licenses and transaction histories for later use. Heavier card stock and paper can also help ensure your loyalty or business cards easily withstand the rigors of regular handling.

seoData.textcontent:
Paper makes the business world go round.
Find paper for every note and document, every form and invitation. It wouldnt be an office without office paper. Good thing Staples carries every paper youll ever need.

Copy paper.
We carry copy paper for everything from everyday documents to your most important reports and marketing collateral. Multipurpose paper is the workhorse of the office a thin and inexpensive paper you can use for everyday jobs. Inkjet paper has a tighter weave to prevent the ink from bleeding through, while laser paper is treated to withstand the heat of the laser printing process. Choose brighter paper for higher profile jobs it will produce sharper text and more vibrant, clearer colors. Print magnets for your business with these inkjet magnetic sheets. And the heavier the weight of your paper, the thicker the pages will be.

Notebooks and notepads.
Notebooks and notepads are ideal for taking notes in meetings, keeping track of to-do lists, and jotting down your brilliant ideas throughout the day. Smaller notebooks can slip inside a pocket or bag, while larger notebooks and notepads provide more room for writing. Perforated pages let you easily tear a page from a notebook or notepad to share it with a colleague.

Journals and diaries.
Journals and diaries offer another format for taking notes, brainstorming, and keeping track of activities from day-to-day. Available in hardcover and softcover formats, journals and diaries offer a more pleasing aesthetic than the more casual feel of notepads and notebooks, and they have a more formal and lasting feel to them. We carry a wide range of products with covers that feature everything from solid colors to abstract patterns, inspirational quotes, and floral or animal themes.

Post-it notes and sticky notes.
These small adhesive notes in a variety of sizes and colors are among the most versatile of office products. In addition to jotting quick notes to oneself or leaving notes for colleagues on stickies, you can use stickies to play with the outline for a speech or paper, to diagram workflows, to brainstorm with colleagues, or to jot down thoughts and tasks that pop into your head that you want to follow up on later.

Index cards and card stock.
Index cards range in size from 2.5 x 3 to 5 x 8 and provide an excellent way to organize everything from reports and notes to people and projects. Card stock has a similar weight to index cards and comes in a variety of colors and finishes. Card stock makes excellent report covers, flyers, and signage.

Forms and POS paper.
Preprinted forms provide instant organizational, financial, and human resources tools. From invoices and receipt books to sales order forms and packing slips, forms boost productivity by formatting the information on a page so that you dont have to. Point-of-sale, or POS paper, is a blank roll of paper designed for printing receipts using cash registers and transaction-style printers. Staples carries a range of sizes and paper qualities, including recycled POS paper.

While youre shopping for paper, dont forget to stock up on pencils, pens, scissors, paper clips and other office basics.

DealsPageSEO.staticPromoMessage2:
Everyone likes to save money, and Staples® My Deals make it simple to find bargains on everything needed to keep a business running, stock a home office, or give students the tools they need to excel. Special offers include personalized deals as well as a broad range of items with universal appeal. Visit the my deals page and find money-saving offers on office supplies, maintenance and cleaning products, office furniture, and more.

Stock Up on Basic Office Supplies
Business professionals and home office users are more effective when they have the tools and accessories they need for the task at hand. Exclusive deals on essential office supplies like copy paper, printer ink and toner, pens, pencils, and notepads reduce overhead costs and ensure everyone in the office can work efficiently. Create a clutter-free workspace with desk organizers, binders, and bookshelves. Organize and store paperwork with folders and file cabinets and use shredders to protect sensitive information when disposing of old records.

Create an Efficient Office
A safe and comfortable work environment enhances productivity and improves morale. Promotional deals on ergonomic office furniture can reduce the cost associated with setting up a new office or replacing worn furniture. Protective gear and office essentials such as first aid kits and cleaning supplies help create hazard-free work environments. Take advantage of special offers on coffee, snacks, sweet treats, and other breakroom supplies to maximize the benefits of employee downtime. Attractive and comfortable reception chairs and tables impress visitors and clients.

Keep Technology Up to Date
Almost everyone has access to a computer or tablet, produces documents with inkjet or laser printers, or uses a network to share information with friends or co-workers. Taking advantage of promotions available on the my deals page makes it simple to keep home, classroom, and office technology up to date. Laptops with plenty of storage and high-resolution displays give students, home users, and business professionals access to the software they need to work effectively. They also provide entertainment when the workday is over. Phones and fax machines keep the lines of communication open, and routers and switches create secure and reliable network connections.

Are My Deals Available in Stores?
While many promotions are available in stores, some deals are only accessible online. In most cases, users can take advantage of next-day delivery to their home or office or choose one-hour, in-store pickup. Select products offer automatic restock options.

How Can Customers Keep up With My Deals?
Special offers change every day, but there are several ways to keep up with new promotions as they become available. Users can visit their my deals page on the website to see current sales or sign up to receive personalized updates via email. They can also like Staples on Facebook® or follow the company on Twitter®.

How Often Do Promotions Change?
New deals show up almost every day, making it easy for savvy shoppers to find good prices on the products they want. Personalized promotions highlight savings on frequently used printing and office supplies. Save money on your next school, work, or household project when you explore the bargains and deals available at Staples.
